    {
      "id": "PopularPost213979",
      "post_content": "Comparing it against targeted removal:  \n  \n Pros: gets around shroud/hexproof, indestructibility and regeneration (although [Dismember](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dismember) has already taken care of the last two).  \n Cons: sucks against tokens/weenies, seems not fill removal's primal role (which would be taking care of that one creature causing you problems, not randomly nomming on a creature).  \n  \nThe life gain from this isn't negligible either, even if it only gains you as much as 3-4 life it helps tipping the game in your favor.  \n  \nAnd things could have been worse for poor Marella. A vampire had some nomz with her daughter, okay. AT LEAST HE DIDN'T GET HER PREGNANT.  \nYeah, my girlfriend dragged me to watch Breaking Dawn (from the Twilight saga).  \n  \n  \n@Edword22: no, she really did, even though knowing of my (and probably of every person with 2 or more functioning brain cells) blatant [despise](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=despise) for sparkly vampires, according to her because \"ROBERT PATTINSON IS SO CUTE!!11\" or something like t... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Lash_of_Dragonbreath",
